{"id": "duc04-testb-32:17#53", "contents": "The prosecution team, led by special counsel David Boies, was not at full strength until shortly before the suit was filed. Boies, a renowned courtroom litigator, did not start working full-time for the Justice Department until mid-April. The antitrust suit filed in May leaned heavily on the Netscape story, but also mentioned Microsoft's tactics against Sun Microsystems, creator of Java. The complaint was crafted as a template that could be added to without much stretching, allowing the government to expand the case as new evidence emerged."}
